## SECTION 4 — SERP ANALYSIS

**Competitor gaps — what they are NOT answering:**
- Most competitors list shades per tone with no explanation of WHY a colour works. No undertone logic, just a list.
- Almost no competitor clearly explains the difference between skin tone (surface) and undertone (beneath) before diving into recommendations — readers get shade lists without the framework to use them.
- The "avoid" guidance is weak or absent across competitors. What to stay away from and why is the biggest gap.
- Finish (crème vs metallic vs jelly) interaction with skin tone is completely absent from competitors.
- Olive skin is the most underserved tone in competitor content — typically a brief mention, rarely a dedicated section.
- The "universally flattering" myth (red, navy, nude) is repeated without nuance. No competitor explains that "universal" only works with undertone alignment.
- Indian / South Asian / wheatish skin tone is absent from nearly all mainstream guides.
- No competitor explains how to swatch or test at the salon before committing.

**Missing semantic territory:**
- Finish impact per skin tone (jelly, crème, metallic, shimmer, chrome)
- Season-to-skin-tone colour logic
- The nail bed test / swatch test as a practical tool
- Undertone identification beyond the vein test (jewellery test, white shirt test)
- Colour psychology of nail shades on different complexions (confidence signals, professional reads)
- How tanning/seasonal change shifts what works

**Our strategic approach:**
This page wins by being the framework guide, not the shade list. Rather than dumping 50 colours per tone, it teaches the logic — undertone first, depth second, finish third. That framework is what keeps readers on-page (solving the bounce rate), converts them into spoke readers (internal linking), and answers AI search queries with direct, citable statements. Every skin tone section must explain WHY as much as WHAT.

**Depth signal:** Top competitors run 1500–2500 words. Our 3000-word target is justified by the breadth of tones covered and the framework depth required to be genuinely useful.

